Mallinus nitidiventris Simon, 1893: 436, figs 409-410 (juv.);
Jocque 1991
: 136, figs 334-335 (juv.).

Morphology and colouration similar to female (Figs 3, 4), except for the following: AME diameter equals 1.16 times ALE diameter; AME separated by distance 0.67 times their diameter; AME separated from ALE by distance 0.38 times AME diameter; clypeus height 3.85 times AME diameter at AME, 4.0 times ALE diameter at ALE; PME diameter equals 0.89 times PLE diameter; PME separated by distance 1.25 times their diameter; PME separated from PLE by distance 1.25 times PME diameter; 
CW
:PERW = 2.17:1. Abdomen relatively smaller than female (Figs 3, 4), shorter than carapace, as high as long, slightly longer than broad, with conspicuous circumferential folds. Palp as in genus description (Figs 44, 48, 49, 52, 53).
